        "option_b_result": "CORRECT - The 'New Status Quo' is the final stage of the Satir Change Model. It is characterized by a new, higher level of performance, where the new process has become the norm and the team is operating in a stable and effective manner. The team's sense of 'pride and accomplishment' further reinforces this.",
        "option_c_result": "INCORRECT - Chaos is the most difficult stage where performance drops and there is a high degree of uncertainty. This is the opposite of the scenario.",
        "option_d_result": "INCORRECT - Resistance is a negative stage that occurs before or during the early stages of a change. The team has already moved past this and is now at a high level of performance.",
