        "option_b_result": "INCORRECT - Updating the Business Case is a key activity, but it's part of ensuring that the project's performance is reviewed. The Business Case is updated to show the final costs and benefits, but this is a component of a larger objective, which is to formally wrap up the project. The primary objective is broader than just a document update.",
        "option_c_result": "CORRECT - The 'Closing a Project' process in PRINCE2 is about the formal administrative closure of the project. Its primary objective is to get final acceptance of the project's products, review the project's performance against its baselines, document and capture lessons learned for the organization, and recommend for the project to be formally closed. This ensures that the project is not just abandoned but is properly wrapped up and knowledge is preserved for the future.",
        "option_d_result": "INCORRECT - The transition of products to operations is a key part of the closure process, but it is a specific activity within the broader 'Closing a Project' process. The primary objective is the formal project closure itself, which includes the transition but also encompasses the performance review and lessons learned. It is a component of the primary objective, not the objective itself.",
        "process_group": "Closing",
